-- Create an environment using terminal
    1. CD to location where you want the env to be installed 
    2. run command python3 -m venv <env_name> 
    3. once in the folder that hosts the application with the env in it run : 
      source <env_name>/bin/activate


-- Running the requirements.txt file:
    1. Run the follwoing command once you have activated your desired environment
    pip install -r requirements.txt
